dsMcastMIB.name: dsMcastMIB
dsMcastMIB.description: The MIB module for Multicast Feature.

DsIgmpVersion.name: DsIgmpVersion
DsIgmpVersion.description: A value that represents the version of IGMP: version1(1) : Version 1 of IGMP version2(2) : Version 2 of IGMP version3(3) : Version 3 of IGMP.

dsIgmpSnoopingChanged.name: dsIgmpSnoopingChanged
dsIgmpSnoopingChanged.description: A dsIgmpSnoopingEnableChanged should be generated when Igmp Snooping is enable or disable

dsIgmpSnoopingVlanChanged.name: dsIgmpSnoopingVlanChanged
dsIgmpSnoopingVlanChanged.description: A dsIgmpSnoopingVlanChanged should be generated when Igmp Snooping Vlan is enable or disable

dsIgmpSnoopingEnabled.name: dsIgmpSnoopingEnabled
dsIgmpSnoopingEnabled.description: This object indicates whether IGMP Snooping has been enabled for the system.

dsFastLeaveEnabled.name: dsFastLeaveEnabled
dsFastLeaveEnabled.description: This object indicates whether Fast-Leave mechanism has been configured to be enabled in the system. If Fast-Leave is enabled in the switch, IGMP Snooping will prune the port on which an IGMP leave message has been received without waiting for the Group Specific Query to timeout to determine whether there are any more hosts on that port for that group. If the value of dsV3ProcessEnabledOperStatus is 'false', this object will not have any effect.

dsFastBlockEnabled.name: dsFastBlockEnabled
dsFastBlockEnabled.description: The object indicates whether Fast-Block mechanism has been enabled for the system. This object only has effect if the value of dsV3ProcessEnabledOperStatus is 'true'.

dsReportSuppressionEnabled.name: dsReportSuppressionEnabled
dsReportSuppressionEnabled.description: When this object is set to 'true', IGMP Snooping will suppress duplicate IGMP Reports. When this object is set to 'false', all IGMP Reports are forwarded to all multicast routers in the VLAN.

dsTopoChangeFloodQueryCount.name: dsTopoChangeFloodQueryCount
dsTopoChangeFloodQueryCount.description: This object specifies the flooding period for multicast traffic upon receiving Topology Change Notifications (TCN). IGMP Snooping will flood multicast traffic until dsTopoChangeFloodQueryCount number of IGMP General Queries are received by IGMP Snooping.

dsTopoChangeQuerySolicitEnabled.name: dsTopoChangeQuerySolicitEnabled
dsTopoChangeQuerySolicitEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the device running IGMP Snooping will solicit IGMP General Queries from the Querier upon receiving a Topology Change Notification (TCN). The root device will always solicit IGMP General Queries on TCN irrespective of the value of dsTopoChangeQuerySolicitEnabled.

dsV3SnoopingSupport.name: dsV3SnoopingSupport
dsV3SnoopingSupport.description: This object indicates IGMP Snooping support for IGMPv3 as described below: basic(1): Basic support for IGMPv3. IGMPv3 packets are processed similar to IGMPv2 packets. In other words Source list information is not used. Although this does not break multicast traffic to IGMPv3 hosts, it does not provide any other benefits such as Fast Leave for IGMPv3 hosts, Explicit Host Tracking and Source based filtering. full(2): Full support for IGMPv3. Provides full IGMPv3 Snooping support. This includes processing of IGMPv3 source list information along with group information. Provides support for features such as Fast Leave, Explicit Host Tracking and Proxy Reporting and a potential to do Source based filtering.

dsIgmpSnoopingGroupCount.name: dsIgmpSnoopingGroupCount
dsIgmpSnoopingGroupCount.description: The count of igmp snooping group entry.

dsMrouteJoinedCount.name: dsMrouteJoinedCount
dsMrouteJoinedCount.description: The count of Mroute Joined channel.

dsInterfaceStatsTable.name: dsInterfaceStatsTable
dsInterfaceStatsTable.description: Table contains statistics information for IGMP snooping. An entry appears in this table for each IGMP Snooping capable interface in the device.

dsInterfaceStatsEntry.name: dsInterfaceStatsEntry
dsInterfaceStatsEntry.description: An entry contains statistics information for a specific IGMP Snooping capable interface. It provides information about IGMP messages and reports that have been transmitted and received at the interface.

dsTxGeneralQueries.name: dsTxGeneralQueries
dsTxGeneralQueries.description: Total IGMP General Queries that have been transmitted through an interface.

dsTxGroupSpecificQueries.name: dsTxGroupSpecificQueries
dsTxGroupSpecificQueries.description: Total IGMP Group-Specific Queries that have been transmitted through an interface.

dsTxReports.name: dsTxReports
dsTxReports.description: Total IGMP Membership Reports that have been transmitted through an interface.

dsTxLeaves.name: dsTxLeaves
dsTxLeaves.description: Total IGMP Leave messages that have been transmitted through an interface.

dsRxGeneralQueries.name: dsRxGeneralQueries
dsRxGeneralQueries.description: Total IGMP General Queries that have been received at an interface.

dsRxGroupSpecificQueries.name: dsRxGroupSpecificQueries
dsRxGroupSpecificQueries.description: Total IGMP Group-Specific Queries that have been received at an interface.

dsRxReports.name: dsRxReports
dsRxReports.description: Total IGMP Membership Reports that have been received at an interface.

dsRxLeaves.name: dsRxLeaves
dsRxLeaves.description: Total IGMP Leave messages that have been received at an interface.

dsRxValidPackets.name: dsRxValidPackets
dsRxValidPackets.description: Total valid IGMP packets have been received at an interface.

dsRxInvalidPackets.name: dsRxInvalidPackets
dsRxInvalidPackets.description: Total packets those are not valid IGMP messages received at an interface.

dsRxOtherPackets.name: dsRxOtherPackets
dsRxOtherPackets.description: Total non IGMP messages messages that have been received at an interface, comprising cgmp join, pim hello, dvmrp and mospf messages.

dsRxTopoNotifications.name: dsRxTopoNotifications
dsRxTopoNotifications.description: Total Topology Change Notifications that have been received at an interface.

dsV3Allows.name: dsV3Allows
dsV3Allows.description: Number of Source-List-Change records with the record type ALLOW_NEW_SOURCES that have been sent from hosts connected to an interface. This record type indicates that the Source Address fields in this Group Record contain a list of additional sources that the system wishes to hear from, for packets sent to the specified multicast address.

dsV3Blocks.name: dsV3Blocks
dsV3Blocks.description: Number of Source-List-Change records with the record type BLOCK_OLD_SOURCE that have been sent from hosts connected to an interface. This record type indicates that the Source Address fields in this Group Record contain a list of the sources that the system no longer wishes to hear from, for packets sent to the specified multicast address.

dsV3IsIncluded.name: dsV3IsIncluded
dsV3IsIncluded.description: Number of Current-State records with the state MODE_IS_INCLUDE that have been sent from hosts in response to a Query received at an interface. This state indicates that the interface has a filter mode of INCLUDE for the specified multicast address.

dsV3IsExcluded.name: dsV3IsExcluded
dsV3IsExcluded.description: Number of Current-State records with the state MODE_IS_EXCLUDE that have been sent from hosts in response to a Query received at an interfaces. This state indicates that the interface has a filter mode of EXCLUDE for the specified multicast address.

dsV3ToIncluded.name: dsV3ToIncluded
dsV3ToIncluded.description: Number of Filter-Mode-Change records with the record type CHANGE_TO_INCLUDE_MODE that have been sent through an interface. This type of record indicates that the filter mode has been changed to INCLUDE mode for the specified multicast address, and the Source Address fields in this Group Record will contain the new source list for the specified multicast address, if it is not empty.

dsV3ToExcluded.name: dsV3ToExcluded
dsV3ToExcluded.description: Number of Filter-Mode-Change records with the record type CHANGE_TO_EXCLUDE_MODE that have been sent through an interface. This type of record indicates that the filter mode has been changed to EXCLUDE mode for the specified multicast address, and the Source Address fields in this Group Record will contain the new source list for the specified multicast address, if it is not empty.

dsVlanConfigTable.name: dsVlanConfigTable
dsVlanConfigTable.description: Table contains VLAN based configuration information for IGMP Snooping.

dsVlanConfigEntry.name: dsVlanConfigEntry
dsVlanConfigEntry.description: An entry is created for each active VLAN in the device and deleted when the VLAN becomes inactive.

dsVlanID.name: dsVlanID
dsVlanID.description: This object indicates the VLAN in which IGMP Snooping is configured.

dsVlanIgmpSnoopingEnabled.name: dsVlanIgmpSnoopingEnabled
dsVlanIgmpSnoopingEnabled.description: When this object is set to 'true' IGMP Snooping is enabled on this VLAN else disabled.

dsVlanFastLeaveEnabled.name: dsVlanFastLeaveEnabled
dsVlanFastLeaveEnabled.description: This object specifies whether Fast-Leave mechanism (also known as Immediate-Leave) is to be performed by IGMP Snooping or not. When enabled, IGMP Snooping will remove the interface from the group mentioned in the IGMP Leave message received on that interface without waiting for the IGMP Group-Specific Query to timeout to determine whether there are any more hosts on that interface for that group.

dsIgmpQuerierTable.name: dsIgmpQuerierTable
dsIgmpQuerierTable.description: Table containing information regarding the IGMP Querier in the VLAN. The device can be configured to be the IGMP Querier for the VLAN. An IGMP Querier for the VLAN is selected by using a Querier Election process.

dsIgmpQuerierEntry.name: dsIgmpQuerierEntry
dsIgmpQuerierEntry.description: An entry is created for each active VLAN in the device and contains IGMP Querier configuration information related to IGMP Snooping for that VLAN. An entry is deleted when the VLAN becomes inactive.

dsIgmpQuerierVlanIndex.name: dsIgmpQuerierVlanIndex
dsIgmpQuerierVlanIndex.description: The object indicates the VLAN that the Querier will send IGMP queries on.

dsIgmpQuerierEnabled.name: dsIgmpQuerierEnabled
dsIgmpQuerierEnabled.description: The object indicates whether the device will participate in the IGMP Querier election in a VLAN. If the object is set to 'true', the device will participate to an election process to be a Querier. If the object is set to 'false' while the device is acting as the Querier in a VLAN, a new election will be activated to choose a different Querier.

dsIgmpQuerierState.name: dsIgmpQuerierState
dsIgmpQuerierState.description: The object indicates the current state of the device as an IGMP Querier in a VLAN. disabled(1) : Querier function is disabled for this device in this VLAN. electing(2) : The device is in the election process of the Querier. querier(3) : The device is the current Querier in this VLAN. nonQuerier(4): The device has lost the election process of the Querier. inactive(5) : VLAN is inactive or not an Ethernet VLAN.

dsIgmpQuerierVersion.name: dsIgmpQuerierVersion
dsIgmpQuerierVersion.description: The object indicates IGMP version of the Querier for the VLAN. IGMP version of the Querier is determined by the type of IGMP General Query received by the device.

dsIgmpQuerierAddress.name: dsIgmpQuerierAddress
dsIgmpQuerierAddress.description: The object indicates IP address of the IGMP Querier for the VLAN.

dsIgmpQuerierPort.name: dsIgmpQuerierPort
dsIgmpQuerierPort.description: The object indicates the interface on which IGMP Querier is detected for the VLAN. The value of this object is zero if the device itself is acting as IGMP Querier for the VLAN.

dsIfConfigTable.name: dsIfConfigTable
dsIfConfigTable.description: Table containing configuration information for IGMP Snooping on a layer two interface.

dsIfConfigEntry.name: dsIfConfigEntry
dsIfConfigEntry.description: An entry is created for each interface layer two interface.

dsIfTopoChangeFloodEnabled.name: dsIfTopoChangeFloodEnabled
dsIfTopoChangeFloodEnabled.description: When this object is set to 'true' multicast traffic will be flooded on the port for dsTopoChangeFloodQueryCount of Igmp General Queries upon receiving a Topology Change Notification (TCN) for the VLAN to which the port belongs.

dsMcastRouterCfgTable.name: dsMcastRouterCfgTable
dsMcastRouterCfgTable.description: Table containing multicast router configuration information for IGMP Snooping.

dsMcastRouterCfgEntry.name: dsMcastRouterCfgEntry
dsMcastRouterCfgEntry.description: An entry is created for each interface in the VLAN that is either learned or configured as multicast router port.

dsMcastRouterVlanIndex.name: dsMcastRouterVlanIndex
dsMcastRouterVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN to which the multicast router port belongs.

dsMcastRouterType.name: dsMcastRouterType
dsMcastRouterType.description: This object indicates if the multicast router port is a configured (static) or learned (dynamic) port.

dsMcastRouterRowStatus.name: dsMcastRouterRowStatus
dsMcastRouterRowStatus.description: This object is a conceptual row entry that allows to add or delete entries to or from the dsMcastRouterCfgTable. When creating an entry in this table 'createAndGo' method is used and the value of this object is set to 'active'. Deactivation of an 'active' entry is not allowed. When deleting an entry in this table 'destroy' method is used.

dsMcastGroupTable.name: dsMcastGroupTable
dsMcastGroupTable.description: Table containing multicast group address information for IGMP Snooping.

dsMcastGroupEntry.name: dsMcastGroupEntry
dsMcastGroupEntry.description: An entry is created by IGMP Snooping for each group learned in the VLAN.

dsMcastGroupVlanIndex.name: dsMcastGroupVlanIndex
dsMcastGroupVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN in which the group is learned.

dsMcastGroupAddress.name: dsMcastGroupAddress
dsMcastGroupAddress.description: This object indicates IP multicast address learned by IGMP Snooping.

dsMcastGroupPortIndex.name: dsMcastGroupPortIndex
dsMcastGroupPortIndex.description: This object indicates the set of ports on which IGMP Membership Reports are received for the group indicating interest to receive traffic sent to the group.

dsMcastGroupFilterMode.name: dsMcastGroupFilterMode
dsMcastGroupFilterMode.description: This object indicates a the IGMP filter mode for the group. include(1) : reception of multicast packets sent to the group specified by cisMcastGroupAddress is requested only from the specified IPv4 source addresses listed in the IGMPv3 Membership Reports. exclude(2) : reception of multicast packets sent to the group specified by cisMcastGroupAddress is requested from all except from the list of IPv4 source addresses specified in the IGMPv3 Membership Reports. The filter mode is determined by the type of Group Record received in the IGMP Membership Report received by the device. Groups for which IGMPv1/v2 Membership Reports are received are considered to have a cisMcastGroupFilterMode of 'exclude'.

dsMcastGroupIgmpVersion.name: dsMcastGroupIgmpVersion
dsMcastGroupIgmpVersion.description: This object indicates the IGMP version for the group. This is determined by the type of IGMP Membership Report received by the device.

dsMcastIgmpGroupTable.name: dsMcastIgmpGroupTable
dsMcastIgmpGroupTable.description: Table containing multicast group address information for IGMP Snooping.

dsMcastIgmpGroupEntry.name: dsMcastIgmpGroupEntry
dsMcastIgmpGroupEntry.description: An entry is created by IGMP Snooping for each group learned in the VLAN.

dsIgmpGroupCount.name: dsIgmpGroupCount
dsIgmpGroupCount.description: The count of igmp group entry.
